'''Elemental chlorine free''' (ECF) is a technique that uses [[chlorine dioxide]] for the [[bleaching of wood pulp]]. It does not use elemental [[chlorine]] gas during the bleaching process and prevents the formation of [[dioxins and dioxin-like compounds]], [[carcinogen]]s.  The traditional ECF sequence is DEopDEpD<ref name="Tool">{{citation
|url=http://www.paperenvironment.org/PDF/chcompounds/CC_Full_Text.pdf |title=Different Bleaching Configurations |publisher=National Council for Air and Stream Improvement |year=2009}}</ref>{{rp|14}} using the common letter symbols for bleaching stages,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.paperonweb.com/bleach.htm|title=PaperOnWeb description of bleaching sequences|accessdate=2007-09-17}}</ref> though many improved sequences are available.<ref name="Tool"/>{{rp|15}}

[[Totally chlorine free]] (TCF) is paper that does not use any chlorine compounds for wood pulp bleaching.

