[[Uruguay]] is a [[petroleum]]-[[import]]ing country.  For decades, Uruguay has been searching for [[petroleum]] reserves on its territory. One of the first such attempts was in 1957, when [[ANCAP (Uruguay)|ANCAP]] drilled in the north of the country.

In 2012, Uruguay engaged on a bidding process for the exploration of [[hydrocarbons]]. The following companies are interested: [[BP]], [[BG Group]], [[Total S.A.]], and [[Tullow Oil]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lr21.com.uy/economia/1030638-hidrocarburos-ancap-firma-contratos-que-consolidan-a-uruguay-en-el-mapa-petrolero-mundial |title=Uruguay on the world petrol map |author= |date=2-4-2012 |work= |publisher=LR21 |accessdate=2 April 2012}}</ref> Soon will begin exploration in offshore platforms, with an investment of over [[United States dollar|$]]1.6 [[1000000000 (number)|billion]] in 3 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lr21.com.uy/economia/1071930-las-cuatro-empresas-que-explotaran-plataforma-maritima-uruguaya-en-busqueda-de-petroleo-invertiran-1-650-millones-de-dolares#|title=4 oil companies interested in offshore drilling|date=6-11-2012|publisher=LR21}}</ref>

